    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sh-Oligopeptide-1 sh-Polypeptide-7 Dipeptide-19 is a synthetic single chain fusion peptide produced by fermentation in  E. coli.  The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the gene from sh-Oligopeptide-1 (q.v.), sh-Polypeptide-7 and Dipeptide-19. The fused peptide contains 244 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
